text: Filer is a city in Twin Falls County, Idaho, United States. In 2020, there were 2,738 people living there. It is just west of the intersection (crossing) of U.S. Route 93 and U.S. Route 30. The town sits on of land. The Twin Falls County Fair is in Filer. It is the city's biggest attraction. ==References== Category:Cities in Idaho Category:Twin Falls County, Idaho
title: Filer, Idaho
